        }
      ],
      "message": "fuzz: share a single mocked steady clock across FuzzedSock instances\n\nEach FuzzedSock used to own its mocked steady clock and call\nMockableSteadyClock::SetMockTime() directly. Hold the clock by reference\nto an externally provided SteadyClockContext instead, so that several\nFuzzedSock instances sharing a test case (e.g. one per peer, or one\ncreated via Accept()) advance a single mocked clock, and the mocking goes\nthrough the SteadyClockContext RAII helper that resets mocktime on\ndestruction.\n\nSteadyClockContext is a LimitOne type, so each fuzz target constructs one\ninstance per iteration and passes it to ConsumeSock / ConsumeNode / the\nFuzzedSock constructor.",
      "committer": {
        "name": "Hao Xu",
        "email": "hao.xu@linux.dev",
        "date": "2026-06-16T07:48:14Z"
      },
      "author": {
        "name": "Hao Xu",
        "email": "hao.xu@linux.dev",
        "date": "2026-06-15T11:35:25Z"
      },
