      "body": "`LimitOne` is an implementation detail, and  I think the last sentence can be removed. Otherwise, all use-sites can explain what `LimitOne` means. If you want to explain it further, a better place would be `SteadyClockContext` itself, so that the docs are only in a single place, instead of spread out.\n\nThe underlying reason is that time is read/written from/to a single global variable. Holding several time contexts for different objects and advancing them independently is simply impossible without changing non-test code. `LimitOne` is just an implementation detail to serve as a linter to avoid violations here and explicitly disallow several time contexts at runtime.",
      "created_at": "2026-06-16T07:11:22Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-06-16T07:12:13Z",
